-- Yahoo Japan Buys CyberAgent Currency-Trade Unit for $254 Million
-- B y   S h i g e r u   S a t o
-- 2012-12-12T08:44:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-12/yahoo-japan-buys-cyberagent-currency-trade-unit-for-254-million.html
Yahoo Japan Corp. (4689) , owner of the
nation’s largest Web portal, acquired  CyberAgent Inc. (4751) ’s foreign-
exchange unit for 21 billion yen ($254 million) to tap
increasing demand for trading on smartphones.  Yahoo  Japan , 35 percent owned by billionaire Masayoshi Son’s  Softbank Corp. (9984) , signed the agreement today with completion
of the deal slated for Jan. 31, the company said in a statement
to the Tokyo Stock Exchange.  Buying Tokyo-based  CyberAgent FX Inc.  will add to Yahoo
Japan’s financial services, which include news and trading
settlements.  CyberAgent FX was formed in September 2003 and held 9.1
billion yen of net assets as of March 31, according to the
statement. CyberAgent operates the  Ameba blogging service .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shigeru Sato in Tokyo at 
